  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Is there an Android application that I can use to lookup words anywhere on my phone, without needing to have the application opened?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several Android applications that allow you to look up words anywhere on your phone without needing to have the app opened. These apps typically provide a feature called \"floating dictionary\" or \"quick lookup\" that allows you to access a dictionary or translator by selecting text or using a gesture. Here are a few popular options:\n\n1. **Google Translate**:\n   - **Feature**: Tap to Translate\n   - **How it works**: When you copy text in any app, a Translate icon appears, allowing you to quickly translate the text.\n\n2. **Dictionary.com**:\n   - **Feature**: Pop-up Definitions\n   - **How it works**: After enabling the feature, you can long-press on any word to get a pop-up definition.\n\n3. **Merriam-Webster Dictionary**:\n   - **Feature**: Merriam-Webster Widget\n   - **How it works**: You can add a widget to your home screen for quick access to the dictionary, and also use the app's quick lookup feature.\n\n4. **Oxford Dictionary of English**:\n   - **Feature**: Oxford Dictionary Widget\n   - **How it works**: Similar to Merriam-Webster, you can add a widget for quick access and use the app's quick lookup feature.\n\n5. **LookUp - English Dictionary**:\n   - **Feature**: Floating Lookup\n   - **How it works**: You can enable a floating bubble that provides quick access to dictionary lookups from anywhere on your phone.\n\n6. **SwiftKey Keyboard** (with Bing Search):\n   - **Feature**: Built-in Search\n   - **How it works**: While typing, you can use the SwiftKey Keyboard to look up definitions from Bing without leaving the app you're in.\n\n7. **Floating Dictionary**:\n   - **Feature**: Floating Window\n   - **How it works**: This app provides a floating window that you can move around your screen and use to look up words instantly.\n\n### How to Enable These Features:\n- **Google Translate**: Go to the app settings and enable \"Tap to Translate.\"\n- **Dictionary.com/Merriam-Webster/Oxford Dictionary**: Look for options like \"Pop-up Definitions\" or \"Widgets\" in the app settings.\n- **LookUp - English Dictionary**: Enable the \"Floating Lookup\" feature in the app settings.\n- **SwiftKey Keyboard**: Enable the \"Bing Search\" feature in the keyboard settings.\n- **Floating Dictionary**: Follow the prompts to enable the floating window when you first launch the app.\n\nThese features can greatly enhance your ability to quickly look up words without interrupting your workflow.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
